external_knowledge:
- "top-spending business customer" refers to the customer who has the highest total amount spent across all their orders;
- "showered the most gold into our coffers" is a metaphor for spending the most money;
- "known birthday and company name" means the customer has a non-null `date_of_birth` and `company_name` in the database.

- "The web of customer relations" refers to the hierarchical structure of customers based on their billing addresses;
- "The most gold" is a metaphor for the highest total revenue;
- "At the root of the hierarchy" indicates the top-level customer in the customer hierarchy.

- "bustling with more than a couple of orders" refers to countries with more than 2 orders;
- "unique souls" refers to unique customers;
- "commercial dance" refers to the process of making orders.

sql:
SELECT 
  (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM customers) AS total_customers,
  (SELECT COALESCE(SUM(total_amount), 0) FROM orders) AS total_revenue;

